**who —** The Baby Metroid — the last Metroid, hatched before Samus in the prior game and stolen from Ceres by Ridley — grown immense in Tourian, it drains Samus, recognizes its 'mother,' returns the energy, and dies attacking Mother Brain

**what —** the last Metroid, hatched before Samus in the prior game and stolen from Ceres by Ridley — grown immense in Tourian, it drains Samus, recognizes its 'mother,' returns the energy, and dies attacking Mother Brain

**where —** SMT · Super Metroid — Nintendo, SNES 1994 (the third Metroid game)  Framework inputs: Super Metroid; Zebes; the baby Metroid; the Power Suit; the descent  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** It is the sacrifice that inverts the hunt: the menace Samus was sent to exterminate gives its life to save her, and its gift becomes the weapon that ends the war.

**how —** Crystallized from Super Metroid (Nintendo, SNES 1994).

**◌ the mythos —** It is the sacrifice that inverts the hunt: the menace Samus was sent to exterminate gives its life to save her, and its gift becomes the weapon that ends the war. a being of the fortress-world Zebes and the silent hunt

**the moniker —** ⟦The Baby Metroid:SMT:4baa17⟧ · spoken *brir-xynd-xor*

**the seal —** the hatchling that imprinted · spiritual

